verbose_text: Sulpiride (50 muM), a more selective D 2 R antagonist [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR] induces a moderate but significant increase of fEPSPs in wild-type (+32.88 +/- 11.71%, n = 8), LoxTAM (+27.32 +/- 12.04%, n = 6), aVMAT2cKO + L-DOPA (+34.38 +/- 15.22%, n = 10) or aVMAT2cKO + lentiVMAT2 mice (+30.54 +/- 6.30%, n = 6) after 40 min application.
